# Claude / agent metadata
.claude/

# Git worktrees (project-local)
.worktrees/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Cargo build output
/target/
**/target/

# Loose work-in-progress notes (not for the repo)
debris/

# proptest shrink-regression corpora (per-test-file, nested)
**/proptest-regressions/

# cargo-fuzz transient output (corpus/ and Cargo.lock ARE committed).
# fuzz/target is already covered by **/target/ above.
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/

# Committed `cargo vendor` tree (reproducible-builds-musl cycle, P3b) — the
# offline reproducible build needs EVERY vendored file. The unanchored rules
# above (`**/target/`, `**/proptest-regressions/`) would otherwise SILENTLY
# exclude real vendored SOURCE files whose SHA-256 is pinned in each crate's
# `.cargo-checksum.json`: `vendor/cc/src/target/*.rs` (the cc crate's target
# DB — a build dep of secp256k1-sys) + any `vendor/*/proptest-regressions/*`.
# A clean checkout missing them FAILS the `--locked --offline` build (empirically:
# `failed to open file vendor/cc/src/target/generated.rs`). Re-include the whole
# vendor tree so the committed checksums resolve. MUST sort AFTER the rules it
# negates (last-match-wins).
!vendor/**
